  "prompt": "What is meant by the hindi term 'bakchodi'?",
  "response": "The Hindi term **'bakchodi'** is a colloquial and informal slang word that can be roughly translated to **\"nonsense,\" \"foolish talk,\"** or **\"time-wasting behavior.\"** It is often used to describe frivolous, nonsensical, or exaggerated conversation or actions that may be seen as a waste of time. In some contexts, it can also imply **mockery, teasing, or banter**, especially when used humorously among friends.\n\nFor example:  \n- **\"Mat kar yeh bakchodi!\"** \u2192 \"Don't do this nonsense!\"  \n- **\"Bakchodi band karo.\"** \u2192 \"Stop fooling around.\"\n\nWhile it\u2019s a commonly used term in informal settings, it can be considered rude or disrespectful in more formal or serious contexts. It\u2019s important to use it carefully depending on the situation and audience.",
